OL,6,FEven though both Mr and Mrs MacGill
OL,7,Fare just making the 182 day target,
OL,8,Fthey say this policy is adding
OL,9,F"enormous strain".
OL,11,FWith rising bills and the cost of
OL,12,Fliving impacting people's holiday
OL,13,Fplans, the couple are living in
OL,14,F"constant stress".
OL,16,FMr MacGill said: "Closure is a
OL,17,Fconcern. If we realise we're going to
OL,18,Ffall short of the 182 target, we'd
OL,19,Fhave to claw back the money somewhere
OL,20,Fto make savings.
